250 g Ground Turkey
6 unit Flour Tortillas
160 g Sweet Bell Pepper
2 unit Green Onion
80 g Tomato
1 unit Lime
56 g Red Onion
1 tbsp Mexican Seasoning
3 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
6 tbsp Sour Cream
½ tsp Sugar*
1.5 cup Mozzarella Cheese, shredded
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Before starting, wash and dry all produce.  Core, then cut pepper into 1/2-inch pieces. Thinly slice green onions. Peel, then cut half the onion into 1/4-inch pieces (whole onion for 4 ppl).Zest, then juice half the lime (NOTE: Whole lime for 4 ppl). Cut any remaining lime into wedges. Cut tomato into 1/4-inch pieces.

Add tomatoes, green onions, half the peppers, half the lime juice and 1/2 tbsp oil (dbl for 4 ppl) to a medium bowl. Season with salt and pepper, then stir to combine.

Add sour cream, lime zest, remaining lime juice and 1/2 tsp sugar (dbl for 4 ppl) to a small bowl. Season with salt and pepper, then stir to combine.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat. When hot, add 2 tsp oil (dbl for 4 ppl), then turkey, onions and remaining peppers. Cook, breaking up turkey into smaller pieces, until no pink remains, 4-5 min.** Add Mexican Seasoning. Cook, stirring often, until fragrant, 30 sec. Remove the pan from heat, then transfer turkey mixture to a large bowl. Add cheese and season with pepper. Stir until combined. Carefully rinse and wipe the pan clean.

Arrange tortillas on a clean surface. Spoon turkey filling evenly over one side of each tortilla. Fold tortillas in half to enclose filling. Heat the same pan over medium. When hot, add 1/2 tbsp oil, then 3 quesadillas. Cook until golden-brown, 1-2 min per side. Repeat with remaining quesadillas.

Cut quesadillas into wedges. Divide quesadillas between plates. Serve lime crema and salsa alongside. Squeeze a lime wedge over top, if desired.